### Migration Logic Summary

The migration is handled entirely inside `getStored()` in `useTheme.ts`:

```
localStorage value "light"  → migrateLegacyThemeValue → "t3-light" → written back to storage
localStorage value "dark"   → migrateLegacyThemeValue → "t3-dark"  → written back to storage
localStorage value "system" → isThemeSelection passes  → "system"   → unchanged
localStorage value "t3-dark" / "t3-light" / "t3-midnight" → pass → unchanged
localStorage missing or unknown → defaults to "system"
```

Migration happens on the very first `getStored()` call, which is at module load time via `applyTheme(getStored())`. This is before the React tree renders, so users who had `"light"` or `"dark"` saved will see the correct theme applied immediately, with no flash.

